title: Lynx
---
A lynx stops Dante in his tracks, forcing him to backtrack. #line:0cd2934
<<task_start Run>>
<<target Hideout>>
<<SetActive false area_hilltop>>
<<SetActive true area_lion>>

//time day
The morning sun shines on Dante, he was not out of danger yet... #line:0ba8eb0
===
title: Lion_and_Wolf
---
Quest Goal - Flee from the Lion and Wolf. #task:flee #line:001f30f

===
title: Virgil_Introduction
---
"Have pity on me, whatever you may be, a shade, a man." #card:Dante #line:0fd5718

"Not man; I once was man. Both of my parents came from Lombardy, and both claimed Mantua as native city. I was a poet, born under false and lying gods." #card:virgilio #line:081e541

"Could you be Virgil? The-" #card:Dante #line:06637f1

"We cannot talk now, the beasts will get to us, let's get moving!" #card:virgilio #line:05e67b5
===
title: Card_DivinaCommedia
---
The structure of the commedia revolves around the number 3. #line:0d54487 
3 is the number for trinity, an holy christian simbol. #line:0ab74c9 
<<card divina_commedia>>
===
title: Card_inferno
---
The structure of Dante's Inferno. #line:0029055 
Dante starts from the Dark Forest to reach the Limbo. #line:0d53e12 
<<card inferno>>
===
title: Card_lion
---
One of the three beasts inside the dark forest. #card:leone #line:0243abf 
Lion sin of pride : one of the seven deadly sins. #card:leone #line:05ce9ec 
<<card leone>>
===
title: Card_lynx
---
One of the three beasts inside the dark forest. #card:lynx #line:0af97fa 
It is the symbol of lust : one of the seven deadly sins. #card:lynx #line:0a46b62 
<<card lynx>>
===
title: Card_shewolf
---
One of the three beasts inside the dark forest. #line:0807462 #card:shewolf
She is the symbol of avarice : the worst sin among the 3. #line:0861662 #card:shewolf
<<card shewolf>>
===
title: Card_Selva
---
A dark forest where dante drifted off to. #card:selva_oscura #line:02562e7 
Its an allegory for sin and cofusion. #card:selva_oscura #line:04ff70b 
<<card selva_oscura>>
===
title: Lynx_Start
---
A spotted lynx slips between the trees, light-footed and quick. It blocks the path and circles you. #card:lynx #line:07b19b4 
<<fight_start>>
===
title: Lynx_Study
---
You watch the lynx's restless circling, trying to read it. #card:lynx #line:0d21a83 
It darts in before you finish the thought. #card:lynx #line:040838e 
<<fight_dodge "lynx_pounce">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    You learn its rhythm, but watching alone changes nothing. It paces, waiting. #card:lynx #line:034a29a 
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: lynx_Provoke
---
You shout and stamp to drive the beast off. #card:lynx #line:0af379c 
The lynx takes it as a game and pounces harder. #card:lynx #line:09f5df5 
<<fight_dodge "lynx_flurry">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    The provocation only sharpens its excitement. It will not be scared away. #card:lynx #line:0010f06 
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: lynx_MatchPace
---
You slow your breathing and let your steps fall into the lynx's own restless rhythm; moving with it, not against it. #card:lynx #line:04097a4 
<<fight_dodge "lynx_pounce">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    The frantic circling eases. Curiosity replaces the hunger in its eyes, and it sits, tail flicking. #card:lynx #line:064fac7 
    <<fight_spare_enable>>
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: lynx_Win
---
The lynx dips its head once, then melts back into the green shadow of the wood. The path ahead is clear. #card:lynx #line:05adc25 
<<camera_focus Hideout_camera>>
We have to reach an Hideout with Dante, lets jump off I will protect us! #card:lynx #line:083d32a 
===
title: lynx_Lose
---
The lynx is too quick, too light. Your strength fails and the dark wood closes over you. #card:lynx #line:0f97d9b 
===

title: Lion_Start
---
Sun's rising and with it a new challenge approaches. #card:leone #line:0f5ac16 
A lion strides from the thicket, head high and mane bristling. #card:leone #line:0d4a543 
It will not yield the road its hunger is for your fear. #card:leone #line:0852dee 
<<fight_start>>
===
title: Lion_RoarBack
---
You square your shoulders and roar back, daring it to come. #card:leone #line:069e0b3 
The lion answers with a charge that shakes the ground. #card:leone #line:0040d72 
<<fight_dodge "lion_charge">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    Pride met with pride only makes it prouder. The lion paws the earth, ready for more. #card:leone #line:036d522 
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Lion_StandTall
---
You hold your ground and refuse to look away. #card:leone #line:0456848 
The lion takes the challenge and presses you hard. #card:leone #line:0b9ae39 
<<fight_dodge "lion_roar">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    Standing firm keeps you alive — but a locked gaze is still a challenge to a proud beast. #card:leone #line:02db46c 
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Lion_ShowHumility
---
You lower your eyes, bow your head, and make yourself no threat at all. #card:leone #line:09ee65d 
<<fight_dodge "lion_roar">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    With no pride to push against, the lion's fury has nowhere to go. Its roar softens to a low, watchful rumble. #card:leone #line:000e7c2 
    <<fight_spare_enable>>
    <<fight_menu>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Lion_Win
---
The lion regards you a long moment, then turns aside with regal grace and lets you pass. #card:leone #line:0172dd9 
===
title: Lion_Lose
---
The lion's pride is a mountain you cannot climb. It overwhelms you, and the road is lost. #card:leone #line:0742e08 
===

title: Trio_Start
---
<<declare $lynx_calm = false>>
<<declare $lion_calm = false>>
<<declare $wolf_calm = false>>
<<set $lynx_calm = false>>
<<set $lion_calm = false>>
<<set $wolf_calm = false>>
The lynx, the lion and the she-wolf step from the wood together and ring you round. Three hungers, one road and no way back. #line:00c4bdc 
Get ready Dante we need to press forward! #card:virgilio #line:03fe9d6 
<<fight_start>>
===
title: Trio_Soothelynx
---
You turn to the restless lynx and fall into its darting rhythm, moving with it until the frenzy drains away. #card:shewolf #line:02af805 
<<fight_dodge "lynx_pounce">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    <<set $lynx_calm = true>>
    The lynx's circling slows; its curiosity is no longer a threat. #card:shewolf #line:02726ac 
    <<jump Trio_AfterSoothe>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Trio_SootheLion
---
You lower your eyes before the lion and offer it no pride to fight. #card:shewolf #line:05b33c6 
<<fight_dodge "lion_charge">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    <<set $lion_calm = true>>
    The lion's roar fades to a watchful rumble. #card:shewolf #line:0532bd0 
    <<jump Trio_AfterSoothe>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Trio_SootheWolf
---
You meet the she-wolf's bottomless hunger with steady, unhurried resolve — wanting nothing she can take from you. #card:shewolf #line:0536568 
<<fight_dodge "wolf_snap">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    <<set $wolf_calm = true>>
    The she-wolf's snarl falters; for once, her hunger finds no purchase. #card:shewolf #line:0bd716e 
    <<jump Trio_AfterSoothe>>
<<endif>>
===
title: Trio_AfterSoothe
---
<<if $lynx_calm and $lion_calm and $wolf_calm>>
    The three beasts circle once more, then settle as one. The road they guarded lies open. #card:shewolf #line:0225504 
    <<fight_spare_enable>>
<<else>>
    One beast is at peace — but the others still pace and snarl, waiting their turn. #card:shewolf #line:0ab066a 
<<endif>>
<<fight_menu>>
===
title: Trio_Win
---
The Beasts draw back together, and the dark wood parts to let you through at last. #card:shewolf #line:05931e2 
Well done Dante, we can proceed further. #card:virgilio #line:0630dfd 
===
title: Trio_Lose
---
Three hungers are too many for one road. The beasts close in, and the way is lost. #card:shewolf #line:057cb53 
===
